The following are major news items in leading Kenyan newspapers on
Wednesday. Kenya Times: -- Kenya's Ministry of Education will ensure
all school are involved in co-curricular activities, providing schools
and neighborhood with recreational facilities to fight drug abuse,
Assistant Minister William Ruto said in Nairobi on Tuesday. East
African Standard: -- About 1,600 Kenyans in the manufacturing sector
are losing their jobs every month, says a report compiled by the Kenya
Association of Manufacturers. The People -- Voting was sluggish in
Uganda's parliamentary election on Tuesday with many saying they saw
little point in another trip to the ballot box soon after re-electing
President Yoweri Museveni overwhelmingly in March.
